  <h1 style="font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem); line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">New articles by email</h1>

  <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Articles here don't arrive on a schedule. They arrive when something real is ready — when a question has been followed far enough to be worth sharing. That might be once a month. It might be less.</p>

  <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">When something new is published, subscribers get a brief note: what the piece is about, what question it starts from, and a link to read it. Nothing else. No sponsorships, no digests, no re-engagement campaigns.</p>

  <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 3rem;">This is a project about consciousness, AI, and what it means that both exist at the same moment in history. If that's a question you're already sitting with, you'll probably want to know when we publish something new.</p>

